===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|ῥάχις||spine, ridge}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɹeɪkɪs/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|rachises|rachides}}

# {{label|en|botany}} The main [[shaft]] of either a [[compound]] [[leaf]], [[head]] of [[grain]], or fern [[frond]].
# {{label|en|zoology|anatomy}} The [[spine]] or the [[vertebrae]] of the spine.
# {{label|en|ornithology}} The [[central]] shaft of a [[feather]].

====Usage notes====
* The plural form {{m|en|rachides}} is technically erroneous, being based on a mistaken impression of the Ancient Greek stem.

